<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14077">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> Check out the Digital Resource Guide for the Communication
      merit badge
      <a
        href="https://www.scouting.org/skills/merit-badges/digital-resource-guides/communication/"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      for detailed information and helpful resources to engage your learning and
      assist you along on your merit badge journey!<br />The official merit
      badge pamphlets are now free and downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Communication.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4799">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4799 mb-requirement-id-4800">
        (a) For one day, keep a log in which you describe your communication
        activities. Keep track of the time and different ways you spend
        communicating, such as talking person-to-person, listening to teachers,
        listening to the radio or podcasts, watching television, using social
        media, reading books and other print media, and using any electronic
        communication device. Discuss with your counselor what your log reveals
        about the importance of communication in your life. Think of ways to
        improve your communication skills. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BW82k7lwI_U" target="_blank"
          >Active Listening (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Communications/Communication%20Log.docx"
          target="_blank"
          >Download a Communication Log Template (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4799 mb-requirement-id-4801">
        (b) For three days, keep a journal of your listening experiences.
        Identify one example of each of the following, and discuss with your
        counselor when you have listened to each: obtain information, be
        persuaded, appreciate or enjoy something, and understand someone's
        feelings. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/x2dxh8xc68E?si=-npAmT7dc7dImnU8"
          target="_blank"
          >Informative Speech (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/lAxMdswA_-s?si=6bkXp98gVYING_RC"
          target="_blank"
          >What is Persuation (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Ljlkvmn0RKk?si=OcaZ410bKns19a4r"
          target="_blank"
          >Want to Add More Joy to Your Life? Here's How (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/_Of_YO0-B4k?si=UmVlPT5mxa25Ud-C"
          target="_blank"
          >Listening Skills for Conflict Resolution (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/D6-MIeRr1e8?si=y9CaTS-PSqosBVdr"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Improve Your Listening Skills (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4799 mb-requirement-id-4802">
        (c) In a small-group setting, meet with other Scouts or with friends.
        Have them share personal stories about significant events in their lives
        that affected them in some way. Take note of how each Scout participates
        in the group discussion and how effectively each Scout communicates
        their story. Report what you have learned to your counselor about the
        differences you observed in effective communication. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/XeJ03dDGlCk?si=RzPTkUkaqKtBDsqI"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Ask Good Questions (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4799 mb-requirement-id-4803">
        (d) List as many ways as you can think of to communicate with others
        (face-to-face, by telephone, letter, email, text messages, social media,
        and so on). For each type of communication, discuss with your counselor
        an instance when that method might not be appropriate or effective.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/2JG9AC0ZxuY?si=dDktq_g5tH8UjIHB"
          target="_blank"
          >Communication Skills (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://scoutlife.org/outdoors/181688/how-to-communicate-underwater-when-scuba-diving/%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Communicating While Scuba Diving (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://scoutlife.org/outdoors/outdoorarticles/3591/calls-for-climbers-and-belayers/"
          target="_blank"
          >Communicating While Climbing (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4804">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4804 mb-requirement-id-4805">
        (a) Think of a creative way to describe yourself using, for example, a
        collage, short story or autobiography, drawing or series of photographs,
        or a song or skit. Using the aid you created, make a presentation to
        your counselor about yourself. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://scoutlife.org/the-emoji-scout-law/" target="_blank"
          >Using Emojis to Communicate the Scout Law (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/xyH79KQET5E?si=VbVYLAd2mcSbj6OQ"
          target="_blank"
          >Writing With Your Audience in Mind (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KVbRQ0cE0Ok?si=dp8uheIh6njAbGy-%20%20"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Use Visual Aids for Public Speaking (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4804 mb-requirement-id-4806">
        (b) Choose a concept, product, or service in which you have great
        confidence. Build a sales plan based on its good points. Try to persuade
        the counselor to agree with, use, or buy your concept, product or
        service. After your sales talk, discuss with your counselor how
        persuasive you were. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/FhWBABCpT9w" target="_blank"
          >Making a Speech Powerful &amp; Persuasive (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4811">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Write a five-minute speech. Give it at a meeting of a group. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/ZFmBcag7G_w?si=GDZyb3cueus0SZ0S" target="_blank"
        >Types of Speeches (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/u-_i7-kNwZI" target="_blank"
        >3 Steps to Write Your Speech (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/_3fz0eiBGvA" target="_blank"
        >How to Overcome the Fear of Public Speaking: 3 Tips (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4812">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Interview someone you know fairly well, like, or respect because of his or
      her position, talent, career, or life experiences. Listen actively to
      learn as much as you can about the person. Then prepare and deliver to
      your counselor an introduction of the person as though this person were to
      be a guest speaker, and include reasons why the audience would want to
      hear this person speak. Show how you would call to invite this person to
      speak. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://speechcoachforexecutives.com/how-to-introduce-your-guest-speaker/"
        target="_blank"
        >How to Introduce Your Guest Speaker (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4813">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Attend a public meeting (city council, school board, debate) approved by
      your counselor where several points of view are given on a single issue.
      Practice active listening skills and take careful notes of each point of
      view. Prepare an objective report that includes all points of view that
      were expressed, and share this with your counselor. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/uy6Eu5l0yOk" target="_blank"
        >3 Note-Taking Methods in 3 Minutes (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://sulky-answer-76a.notion.site/Note-taking-assignment-tips-52758bb0f5a3486181c4b60b813e0338"
        target="_blank"
        >Note-Taking Assignment Tips (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4814">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      With your counselor's approval, develop a plan to teach a skill or inform
      someone about something. Prepare teaching aids for your plan. Carry out
      your plan. With your counselor, determine whether the person has learned
      what you intended. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/WAAuRoz4pVc" target="_blank"
        >Scouting's Teaching EDGE (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4807">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4807 mb-requirement-id-4808">
        (a) Write to the editor of a magazine or your local newspaper to express
        your opinion or share information on any subject you choose. Send your
        message by fax, email, or regular mail. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://scoutlife.org/contact-us/communications-mb/%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Link to Write to the Editors of Scout Life (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yxflXSfOalk" target="_blank"
          >How to Write a Letter to the Editor (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4807 mb-requirement-id-4809">
        (b) Create a webpage or blog of special interest to you (for instance,
        your troop or crew, a hobby, or a sport). Include at least three
        articles or entries and one photograph or illustration, and one link to
        some other webpage or blog that would be helpful to someone who visits
        the webpage or blog you have created.<br /><b>Note:</b> It is not
        necessary to post your webpage or blog to the internet, but if you
        decide to do so, you must first share it with your parent or guardian
        and counselor and get their permission. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0woNTtlcxgM" target="_blank"
          >How to Use Google Sites - Tutorial for Beginners (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/A2ky3irNAiw" target="_blank"
          >Build a Website in Canva &amp; Host it for FREE (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.easybib.com/" target="_blank"
          >Get Your Paper Hand-In Ready (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://vimeo.com/1154745256/49c11cda51?fl=pl&amp;fe=vl"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Proofready Your Blog (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4807 mb-requirement-id-4810">
        (c) Use desktop publishing to produce a newsletter, brochure, flyer, or
        other printed material for your troop or crew, class at school, or other
        group. Include at least one article and one photograph or illustration.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DWiM3GLw0Z8" target="_blank"
          >Canva Brochure Design Tutorial (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7eeUsOQI5EA" target="_blank"
          >How to Make a FLYER in Google Docs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pPYcPlTFbwU" target="_blank"
          >How to Use Lucidpress to Make a Pamphlet or Brochure (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4815">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Plan a troop or crew court of honor, campfire program, or an interfaith
      worship service. Have the patrol leaders' council approve it, then write
      the script and prepare the program. Serve as master of ceremonies.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a
        href="https://troopleader.scouting.org/program-features/"
        target="_blank"
        >Troop Program Features (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://troopleader.scouting.org/program-features/communication/"
        target="_blank"
        >Program Feature: Communication (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://troopleader.scouting.org/ceremonies/troop-courts-of-honor/"
        target="_blank"
        >Troop Courts of Honor (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://troopleader.scouting.org/ceremonies/eagle-courts-of-honor/"
        target="_blank"
        >Eagle Courts of Honor (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/pdf/33696.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >Campfire Planning form (PDF)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://dragon.sleepdeprived.ca/songbook/campfire_planning.htm"
        target="_blank"
        >Campfire Planning (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/pdf/Interfaithservice.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >Interfaith Worship Service (PDF)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4816">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Find out about three career opportunities in communication. Pick one and
      find out the education, training, and experience required for this
      profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this
      profession might interest you.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
